BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ace-pice-movilidad-2026-fase3@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163025Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260907
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260908
SUMMARY:Deadline: Accion Cultural Espanola: PICE Movilidad 2026 (Phase 3)
DESCRIPTION:PICE Movilidad is AC/E's collaboration scheme with foreign cult
 ural institutions: a festival\, biennial\, museum\, venue\, gallery or pla
 tform OUTSIDE Spain applies for AC/E to cover the costs of programming Spa
 nish or Spain-resident artists\, collectives and cultural professionals in
  its own public programme. This is one of the clearest routes for a non-Sp
 anish festival to have a foreign national fund pay for part of its program
 me. Ten thematic areas are covered including Artes visuales\, Musica y cre
 acion sonora\, Podcast\, Videojuego y animacion and Arquitectura y diseno\
 , so tech-crossover\, sound-art and media-art programming is squarely in s
 cope. For visual arts and architecture/design\, covered costs include prod
 uction materials\, purchase or rental of technical equipment\, hiring of t
 echnicians\, curators\, coordinators and designers\, reproduction and exhi
 bition rights\, logistics and transport of works\, publications\, document
 ation\, accommodation\, per diems\, travel and insurance\; for Musica y cr
 eacion sonora coverage is narrower (travel\, accommodation\, per diems\, i
 nternal transport). Non-EU and UK organisations are fully eligible\; there
  is no EU-membership requirement. Natural persons are barred. TIMING: Phas
 e 3 closes 7 September 2026\, provisional list 21 October\, definitive awa
 rd list 30 October\, and Phase 3 projects may not begin before 1 November 
 2026\, so this window cannot retro-fund an event already scheduled for aut
 umn 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Accion Cultural Espanola (AC/E)\nLocation: Anyw
 here outside Spain\, at the applicant's own venue or event. Applicant must
  be a foreign entity constituted outside Spain.\nAward: Max EUR 15\,000 pe
 r applicant per call\, per event and per thematic area\; within that\, max
  EUR 5\,000 per participant or collective. Total 2026 call budget EUR 1\,8
 10\,000 (Musica y creacion sonora EUR 320\,000\, Artes visuales EUR 200\,0
 00\, Videojuego y animacion EUR 90\,000\, Arquitectura y diseno EUR 90\,00
 0\, Podcast EUR 90\,000). Mandatory co-financing: the applicant must commi
 t at least 50 percent of each proposal's total budget. No application fee.
 \nDuration: Single event or project\; Phase 3 activities must start on or 
 after 1 November 2026 and finish before 28 February 2027.\n\nMore: https:/
 /www.accioncultural.es/es/movilidad-2026?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrant
 desk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.accioncultural.es/es/movilidad-2026?utm_source=artificialno
 uveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Anywhere outside Spain\, at the applicant's own venue or event. Ap
 plicant must be a foreign entity constituted outside Spain.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:revitalizing-rituals-2026-open-call@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163025Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260719
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260720
SUMMARY:Deadline: Revitalizing Rituals 2026 Open Call
DESCRIPTION:Revitalizing Rituals invites artists from all disciplines -- so
 und\, movement\, visual arts\, installation\, performance\, and transdisci
 plinary practices -- to join a research-creation journey across two landsc
 apes: Bhar Lazreg in Tunisia and the wetlands of Somogy County in Hungary.
  The project explores rituals as living forms of belonging: reconnecting c
 ommunities\, land\, memory\, food\, ecological reciprocity\, and the more-
 than-human world. Selected artists work with local communities as co-parti
 cipants in a shared inquiry into moving from extraction toward reciprocity
 . Organised by Homo Faber Alapítvány (Hungary). AMOUNT: EUR 6\,000 gross
  artist fee and production budget\; international travel and per diems cov
 ered\; on-site accommodation provided. ELIGIBILITY: minimum 5 years of act
 ive artistic practice\; portfolio reflecting interest in situated or relat
 ional work\; no formal degree required\; working language is English (loca
 l language navigation valued)\; must be available for the full residency c
 ycle including all international travel\; must be able to legally receive 
 the fee and invoice the organising partners from country of residence. Str
 ongly encourages applications from historically marginalised or underrepre
 sented voices. KEY DATES: Application Deadline 19 July 2026 (midnight) -- 
 note the open call PDF also references a 5 July date\; the officially prom
 oted deadline is 19 July\; Online Q&A 29 June 2026\, 14:00 Tunisia / 15:00
  CET (register at https://forms.gle/brnZvXvFe4JB8zL26)\; Online Conversati
 ons with shortlisted artists: mid July to mid August 2026\; Selection Resu
 lts: 31 August 2026\; Placemaking Camp: 1 week\, end of November 2026\, Hu
 ngary\; Storytellers Camp: 1 week\, March 2027\, Tunisia\; Residency Perio
 d: minimum 1 month (splittable)\, April to July 2027\; Final Presentation:
  August 2027\; Closing Event: 3 days\, winter/early spring 2028\, Hungary.
  Apply via the open call form linked at https://homofaber.hu/wp-content/up
 loads/2026/06/Artist-Open-Call-FINAL-in-the-RR-form.pdf.\n\nOrganisation: 
 Homo Faber Alapítvány (Homo Faber Foundation)\nLocation: Bhar Lazreg\, T
 unisia and Somogy County\, Hungary\; multi-stage in-person residency acros
 s both sites.\nAward: EUR 6\,000 gross artist fee and production budget\; 
 international travel and per diems covered\; on-site accommodation provide
 d. No application fee.\nDuration: Multi-stage residency: Placemaking Camp 
 (1 week\, November 2026\, Hungary)\; Storytellers Camp (1 week\, March 202
 7\, Tunisia)\; Residency Period (minimum 1 month\, April-July 2027)\; publ
 ic presentation (August 2027)\; Closing Event (3 days\, winter/early sprin
 g 2028\, Hungary).\n\nMore: https://homofaber.hu/wp-content/uploads/2026/0
 6/Artist-Open-Call-FINAL-in-the-RR-form.pdf?utm_source=artificialnouveaugr
 antdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://homofaber.hu/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Artist-Open-Call-FINAL-
 in-the-RR-form.pdf?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referr
 al
LOCATION:Bhar Lazreg\, Tunisia and Somogy County\, Hungary\; multi-stage in
 -person residency across both sites.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:adk-ems-berlin-stockholm-residency-2026-27@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T163025Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260731
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
SUMMARY:Deadline: AdK / EMS Berlin-Stockholm Bilateral Residency Program 20
 26-27
DESCRIPTION:A new bilateral residency collaboration between the Studio für
  Elektroakustische Musik at the Akademie der Künste in Berlin and Elektro
 nmusikstudion EMS in Stockholm. Four artists will be selected to develop a
 nd present new works in both cities\, with presentations at KONTAKTE 2027 
 in Berlin and at a corresponding event in Stockholm. The program supports 
 new artistic and technical initiatives at the intersection of sound\, musi
 c\, and technology in the field of time-based\, performative\, and digital
  arts. ELIGIBLE CATEGORIES: (1) new instrumental and live-electronic works
 \; (2) acousmatic music\, computer music\, radio art\, and other forms of 
 electroacoustic music and sound art\; (3) projects from artists of any dis
 cipline for whom sound is a central element\; (4) curatorial\, publishing\
 , and educational projects in sound-based art practice\, particularly thos
 e relating in content to the AdK Studio or EMS\; (5) independent research 
 in acoustics\, computer science\, or musicology -- specifically software d
 evelopment\, spatialization\, or network technologies. Open to individuals
  and groups. Project duration is flexible and arranged by agreement. SUPPO
 RT: travel and accommodation costs for Berlin and Stockholm covered\; pres
 entation fees paid for both venues. Selection is made by the director and 
 advisory board of the Studio für Elektroakustische Musik and the director
  of EMS\; decision is final with no legal entitlement to funding. Incomple
 te or late applications are not considered. This call supplements the Stud
 io's regular residency program (separate deadline June 30\, 2026 for July-
 December 2026 period). Apply exclusively via the online form at https://nc
 .adk.de/index.php/apps/forms/s/HD2nxbzqwgeMHWN6xHg9bQrA. Questions: estudi
 o@adk.de. Deadline: 31 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Studio für Elektroakus
 tische Musik\, Akademie der Künste (Berlin) and Elektronmusikstudion EMS 
 (Stockholm)\nLocation: Berlin\, Germany and Stockholm\, Sweden\; travel an
 d accommodation covered for stays in both cities.\nAward: Travel and accom
 modation costs for stays in Berlin and Stockholm covered\; fees paid for p
 resentation at KONTAKTE Festival 2027 (Berlin) and for presentation in Sto
 ckholm. Amount not publicly stated. No application fee.\nDuration: Flexibl
 e\, by agreement\; works to be presented at KONTAKTE 2027 in Berlin and at
  a Stockholm presentation.\n\nMore: https://nc.adk.de/index.php/apps/forms
 /s/HD2nxbzqwgeMHWN6xHg9bQrA?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medi
 um=referral
URL:https://nc.adk.de/index.php/apps/forms/s/HD2nxbzqwgeMHWN6xHg9bQrA?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany and Stockholm\, Sweden\; travel and accommodation
  covered for stays in both cities.
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
